Key Match Events: Joel Embiid delivered a dominant performance with a double-double, featuring 28 points and 12 rebounds, powering the 76ers to a commanding 123-94 victory.
Paul George supported Embiid with an impressive performance, finishing with 17 points, four rebounds, six assists, and two steals.
Tyrese Maxey added to the effort with 18 points and seven assists.
Ziaire Williams posted 19 points, three rebounds, and two assists for the Nets.
Newly-acquired Nets guard D'Angelo Russell contributed five points and played just 14 minutes before exiting the game with a right shin contusion.
The Nets opened the game with an 11-0 run, but the 76ers roared back to secure a 29-19 lead by the end of the first quarter.
Philadelphia's Caleb Martin scored eight points in the second quarter to help the 76ers extend their lead to 64-47 heading into halftime.
